[
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.1",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 1,
    "text": "[A Psalm of Asaph.] Truly God {is} good to Israel, {even} to such as are of a clean heart. {of: or, for} {Truly: or, Yet} {of...: Heb. clean of heart}",
    "hash": "b383350ca407ed1e201a28b6e70e6325d5088a0cef3596786b5ed34a2ae5a8bd"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.2",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 2,
    "text": "But as for me, my feet were almost gone; my steps had well nigh slipped.",
    "hash": "0d681a5be083946ec729780472639b8a2cd2e598b5976444c5b138a1756f735d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.3",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 3,
    "text": "For I was envious at the foolish, {when} I saw the prosperity of the wicked.",
    "hash": "9665ee43ddad206e3c9a40901e202ecc041c939bbcbddc494e61e9a157ce57e6"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.4",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 4,
    "text": "For {there are} no bands in their death: but their strength {is} firm. {firm: Heb. fat}",
    "hash": "3514976f630a6c701bf6c1c01a2ceea40f1828c9e97dbf2f509e1a85d605e9e1"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.5",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 5,
    "text": "They {are} not in trouble {as other} men; neither are they plagued like {other} men. {in...: Heb. in the trouble of other men} {like: Heb. with}",
    "hash": "313a9e6583b6f9cffe961c17c49f56ceabbbaf9adf3407b7f3d0a6eb23fd6e9b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.6",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 6,
    "text": "Therefore pride compasseth them about as a chain; violence covereth them {as} a garment.",
    "hash": "4a3b86944ddbe91c43a745c5f4653b40a548c10da503aece4a6c4e8ebfd9b714"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.7",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 7,
    "text": "Their eyes stand out with fatness: they have more than heart could wish. {have...: Heb. pass the thoughts of the heart}",
    "hash": "1c57f8485e66ce3429ffe27041b22bbead4a475c03da535131f3606f29b02fc9"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.8",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 8,
    "text": "They are corrupt, and speak wickedly {concerning} oppression: they speak loftily.",
    "hash": "6bff53b3ec718544a80376ea5d638e8465be3f531ce6916359ed12e2f8a4d89a"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.9",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 9,
    "text": "They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walketh through the earth.",
    "hash": "a198f83cd4360897537744081eb4976f3e066fc0e986fcd7603d2ba125d3542c"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.10",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 10,
    "text": "Therefore his people return hither: and waters of a full {cup} are wrung out to them.",
    "hash": "2688a794acbb64696e01fffb8b14a0916f2a1ae269a1cad6f82aecc7784d2214"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.11",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 11,
    "text": "And they say, How doth God know? and is there knowledge in the most High?",
    "hash": "e0de4b0cf55ca0726764617d5789379b9bad8edf1f48acf7b0825f7b871e0428"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.12",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 12,
    "text": "Behold, these {are} the ungodly, who prosper in the world; they increase {in} riches.",
    "hash": "a477a5a113e4c52d13e8b7c04f387d1fb10e5d69bb27ddf3b4af7784014e3a9b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.13",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 13,
    "text": "Verily I have cleansed my heart {in} vain, and washed my hands in innocency.",
    "hash": "58dc72aaaf4c9430b1b03d4e4ce9149f4910b05b8aa489eb5c4be00b481a95fd"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.14",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 14,
    "text": "For all the day long have I been plagued, and chastened every morning. {chastened: Heb. my chastisement was}",
    "hash": "9930a1c05d2c4a479034a92d6300a00da55b05cb297312cafe87c03cce8464c0"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.15",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 15,
    "text": "If I say, I will speak thus; behold, I should offend {against} the generation of thy children.",
    "hash": "b93d3677c45a0a48097031bc5caf3fe3b854e0c4e0c79f4ceb1dc502b395431f"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.16",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 16,
    "text": "When I thought to know this, it {was} too painful for me; {too...: Heb. labour in mine eyes}",
    "hash": "ac44f533c5b3f55ff4205f9fcbcd8cff1c3d233ebc8d366218e88652e012f6ab"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.17",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 17,
    "text": "Until I went into the sanctuary of God; {then} understood I their end.",
    "hash": "3eb5a963bfbe53837f4c63a1d9c42212947e27603b80220e70d6cbd0235f8f0d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.18",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 18,
    "text": "Surely thou didst set them in slippery places: thou castedst them down into destruction.",
    "hash": "0068823d419c821a73f51fdd4a13e345b4063755bbe00c72877bff8aba07194b"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.19",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 19,
    "text": "How are they {brought} into desolation, as in a moment! they are utterly consumed with terrors.",
    "hash": "d572f0da1a3a110e7a25dc8da6d3158e7617cf0eb30e1356395ceda19b767a02"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.20",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 20,
    "text": "As a dream when {one} awaketh; {so}, O Lord, when thou awakest, thou shalt despise their image.",
    "hash": "1f012b15591526d71f8fd19899df178f2065b074d6725b584ebed532e85016a5"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.21",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 21,
    "text": "Thus my heart was grieved, and I was pricked in my reins.",
    "hash": "00c9e60f2ccc8d4301b5ac5697fb3c54986d3ffdd2c34cb1d6d8549252793368"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.22",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 22,
    "text": "So foolish {was} I, and ignorant: I was {as} a beast before thee. {ignorant: Heb. I knew not} {before Heb. with}",
    "hash": "8a61ea0a05e0439a92f30f102aa5ff49664d4807f712137717340598d010378d"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.23",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 23,
    "text": "Nevertheless I {am} continually with thee: thou hast holden {me} by my right hand.",
    "hash": "40762e7cf1551c3a5300c5bad84a3160d6ec821bd8608d6484221eafa50c4ddf"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.24",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 24,
    "text": "Thou shalt guide me with thy counsel, and afterward receive me {to} glory.",
    "hash": "c491cb1abf54a642b3cbc169afbf861d23e525bfc53e741b338fec31fa6e09c8"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.25",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 25,
    "text": "Whom have I in heaven {but thee}? and {there is} none upon earth {that} I desire beside thee.",
    "hash": "119540f78997b94ef7836a20cd01c569c35eac0b2fc1aeafc811bc2001fb7233"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.26",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 26,
    "text": "My flesh and my heart faileth: {but} God {is} the strength of my heart, and my portion for ever. {strength: Heb. rock}",
    "hash": "ad4ac701d0fe4bd9192ee5a89a58c33253255d5a1ace20c20d5077b953e120e0"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.27",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 27,
    "text": "For, lo, they that are far from thee shall perish: thou hast destroyed all them that go a whoring from thee.",
    "hash": "5de810865efee9013fc6afb8e8d4557f222b907c0b632886e0e6c4758e978c66"
  },
  {
    "id": "PSA.73.28",
    "book": "Psalms",
    "bookNum": 19,
    "bookAbbrev": "PSA",
    "chapter": 73,
    "verse": 28,
    "text": "But {it is} good for me to draw near to God: I have put my trust in the Lord GOD, that I may declare all thy works.",
    "hash": "8d3b4d92e46daecdf8329772433a5d1d32318b6e2b3abbbc9d00c26309ce5cf2"
  }
]